OL,3,CInside the meeting of two Post Office
OL,4,Cscandal victims we helped bring
OL,5,Ctogether
OL,7,FBut it was beautiful. It felt like
OL,8,Feverything around them melted away and
OL,9,Fthey only had eyes for each other. In
OL,10,Ffact, Betty's eyes were very emotional
OL,11,Fand I could see she looked at Chris
OL,12,Fnot only with admiration for all his
OL,13,Fcampaigning but with warmth, too.
OL,15,FSeeing them both sat together was a
OL,16,Fbit surreal, if only because seeing
OL,17,Ftheir vast age difference reminds you
OL,18,Fthat the Horizon scandal was
OL,19,Findiscriminate about who suffered.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/9
